In <2oti6l$p5g@lyra.csx.cam.ac.uk> rja14@cl.cam.ac.uk (Ross Anderson) writes:

>However in the case of the U-boats it was impractical to give each boat 
>its own key, as the boats had to communicate with each other while hunting
>in packs, and with `mother' ships to be resupplied at sea.

>Ross

Towards the end of the war U-boats that were not operating in
"Wolfpacks" were issued with their own key. Refueling and resupply
was handled via U-boat control which was the normal method. The
resupply/tanker (Milk cows) ships were supposed to keep radio
silence during resupply operations.

Frode 
